        "type": "message",
        "text": "Partial disagree about leaving disconnected wires around. I agree that you should be able to have one end loose, but if you can fully disconnect them I worry they'll clutter the workspace. I can imagine myself hooking a nearby wire end to a node and wondering why it doesn't work, forgetting that I also disconnected the other end some other time (maybe a visual indicator of the other end's status would be good enough?). So I would rather wires be disposable commodities, but that would clash with your idea of annotations/comments etc on wires. Thoughts on this?",
